text:
Kellye Nakahara (January 16, 1948 – February 16, 2020) was an American actress. She was best known for playing Nurse Kealani Kellye in 165 episodes of the television comedy "M*A*S*H". She was born in Oahu, Hawaii.
Nakahara died from cancer at her home in Pasadena, California on February 16, 2020, at age 72.
